  "prompt": "What does dark humor mean?",
  "response": "Dark humor, also known as black humor or gallows humor, is a style of comedy that finds humor in subjects that are generally considered serious, taboo, or sensitive. These may include topics related to death, illness, tragedy, and other distressing themes. Dark humor often plays on the juxtaposition of morbid or grim subjects with a lighthearted or sardonic delivery, challenging societal norms and expectations about what is considered appropriate. This type of humor can be controversial, as it may be perceived as offensive or insensitive, but it can also provide a way for people to cope with difficult situations by laughing at the absurdity or inevitability of certain aspects of life.",
